column1: This column is used to uniquely identify each row on this worksheet. User Stories in a given Sprint are traced back to the Product Backlog using the User Story ID to the details on the Sprint Backlog Product Backlog ID
column2: This column documents the source from which the expanded requirement came (e.g., statement of work, change request, work session, standards document etc.). Source
column3: Column to prioritize requirements using MoSCoW) - Must Have, Should Have, Could Have, Won't Have Priority (M/S/C/W)
column4: Column for uniquely identifying the use case, Originates from Use case Model [RA.023] When used Corresponds to a use case number on the Use Case Catalog sheet. Note - Requirements satisfied by COTS applications that are defined in SOW are assigned a use case in order to create traceability. Not required for requirements satisfied by the COTS App that are not in SOW. User Story ID
column5: Brief description of the requirements necessary to fulfill the objective User Story Name
column6: Column used to identify owner of requirement as defined by SOW and/or supporting documentation. Defined assumptions are treated as requirements owned by designated party. User
column7: Column used to identify owner of requirement as defined by SOW and/or supporting documentation. Defined assumptions are treated as requirements owned by designated party. Scrum Team Assigned
column8: Complexity of the functional requirement. Very Simple Simple Average Complex Very Complex Complexity
column9: Technical, Organizational, External project risk associated with the requirement. This is further detailed in the Project Risk Management Plan. What is the probability that something will go wrong in meeting the requirement? A risk might happen, or it might not; there is some uncertainty. Use H (High), M (Medium), L (Low). Risk/ Impact
column10: Defines whether the User Story is Functional, Non-Functional or Technical type.  Type
column11: This column is used to link the User Story to the User Acceptance test scenarios that validate the requirement was satisfied. User Acceptance Test Case ID
column12: This column is used to provide supporting information, such as changes to the original requirement.  Comments
